@NODE distribute "StopMenu Documentation - Legal Issues"


@{b}3. Legal Issues@{ub}


@{b}Distribution@{ub}

StopMenu is @{b}Shareware@{ub}. You can use the unregistered version for 3 weeks for
evalution purposes. After this time you should either @{"register" LINK register} (prefered) or
delete the program from your hard disk. Upon registering you will receive a
keyfile which will disable the annoying requesters.

The demo version (without the keyfile) may be freely distributed as long as you
keep the archive unmodified and don't try to make profit out of it. If you
include it on a cover disk or a cover CD you should ask for my permission first.
It would also be great if you would send me a free copy of the magazine, which
featured my program on the cover disk or CD.

You are not allowed to distribute the registered version (i.e. the keyfile). It
is meant only for your personal use. Any further distribution of the keyfile is
considered as an act of software piracy.

THE PROGRAM IS AVAILABLE AS-IS. THE AUTHOR DOES NOT WARRANT THAT IT WILL
FUNCTION PROPERLY ON YOUR COMPUTER. YOU ARE USING IT AT YOUR OWN RISK, I AM NOT
RESPONSIBLE FOR ANY LOSS OF DATA OR PROFIT OR ANY OTHER DAMAGES THAT MIGHT
OCCUR BECAUSE OF THIS PROGRAM.

(C)1998-1999 Tomasz Wójcik, (C)1999-2000 Damir Arh, All Rights Reserved.


